Text: NYSRC ICAP WG Telecon March th Cc The ICAP Working Group of the New York State Reliability Council NYSRC is posting this message to inform all interested parties of the ability to participate on a listenonly basis in the NYSRC ICAP Working Group teleconference No scheduled for March starting at AM Attached in Word format is the Agenda for this teleconference The Working Groups open teleconference is in accordance with NYSRC Policy No which is available of the NYSRC web site at wwwnysrcorg on the Policies web page Those wishing to participate on a listenonly basis can call and enter participant Code starting at AM Participants will be required to place their telephones on mute so as not to prevent other parties from participating Those who plan on listening to the meeting shall send an email to my attention at with the names of the individuals and organizations participating Participants who are not NYSRC ICAP WG Members or Alternate Members will be given an opportunity to comment at the end of each teleconference or earlier at the Chairmans invitation Should you have any questions please contact me by email at or by phone at Kevin M Donnelly Secretary NYSRC ICAP WG See attached file NYSRC ICAP WG Agenda CCdoc NYSRC ICAP WG Agenda CCdoc You are currently subscribed to nyisotie as To unsubscribe send a blank email to

NYSRC ICAP WG Metting Cc The ICAP Working Group under the New York State Reliability Council NYSRC is posting this message to inform all interested parties of the ability to attend in person or participate on a listenonly basis in the NYSRC ICAP Working Groups Meeting No scheduled for October starting at AM at the ISOs Washington Avenue extension Attached in Word format is the Agenda for this meeting The NYSRC has opened its Committee Subcommittee and Working Group meetings in accordance with NYSRC Policy No tcwebpdfPolicyFinalpdf Those who plan on attending the meeting in person are requested to contact me at least seven days in advance of the meeting by at least October th by sending me an email at with the names of the individuals organizations attending Meeting space will be available on a firstcome firstserved basis due to the space limitations of the conference rooms Those wishing to participate on a listenonly basis can call and enter Participant Code Participants will be required to place their telephones on mute so as not to prevent other parties from participating Those who plan on listening to the meeting shall send an email to my attention at with the names of the individuals organizations participating Attendees who are not NYSRC Executive Committee Members or Alternate Members will be given an opportunity to comment at the end of the Open Session of each meeting or earlier at the Chairmans invitation Should you have any questions please contact me by email at or by phone at Michael P Hogan Secretary NYSRC ICAP WG Agenda See attached file NYSRC ICAP WG Agenda MtgdocSee attached file NYSRC ICAP WG Agenda Mtgdoc NYSRC ICAP WG Agenda Mtgdoc

NYSRC ICAP WG Mtg location change Cc The location of the following meeting has been changed to the NYISO office at Washington Avenue Extension Conference Room D This change was necessary to accommodate the number of attendees The ICAP Working Group of the New York State Reliability Council NYSRC is posting this message to inform all interested parties of the ability to attend in person or participate on a listenonly basis in the NYSRC ICAP Working Group Meeting No scheduled for August starting at AM at the New York Independent System Operators Power Control Center in Guilderland NY Attached in Word format is the Agenda for this meeting The Working Group is an open meeting in accordance with NYSRC Policy No which is available of the NYSRC web site at wwwnysrcorg on the Policies web page Those who plan on attending the meeting in person are requested to contact me at least three working days in advance of the meeting by at least August th by sending me an email at with the names of the individuals organizations attending Meeting space will be available on a firstcome firstserved basis due to the space limitations of the conference rooms Those wishing to participate on a listenonly basis can call and enter articipant Code starting at AM Participants will be required to place their telephones on mute so as not to prevent other parties from participating Those who plan on listening to the meeting shall send an email to my attention at with the names of the individuals and organizations participating Attendees who are not NYSRC ICAP WG Members or Alternate Members will be given an opportunity to comment at the end of each meeting or earlier at the Chairmans invitation Should you have any questions please contact me by email at or by phone at Michael P Hogan Secretary NYSRC ICAP WG See attached file NYSRC ICAP WG Agenda MtgdocSee attached file NYSRC ICAP WG Agenda Mtgdoc See attached file NYSRC ICAP WG Agenda Mtgdoc NYSRC ICAP WG Agenda Mtgdoc

NYSRC ICAP WG conf call Cc writes to the NYISOTECHEXCHANGE Discussion List The ICAP Working Group of the New York State Reliability Council NYSRC is posting this message to inform all interested parties of the ability participate on a listenonly basis in the NYSRC ICAP Working Group Conference Call No scheduled for September starting at AM The Working Group is an open meeting in accordance with NYSRC Policy No which is available of the NYSRC web site at wwwnysrcorg on the Policies web page Those wishing to participate on a listenonly basis can call and enter participant Code starting at AM Participants will be required to place their telephones on mute so as not to prevent other parties from participating Those who plan on listening to the meeting shall send an email to my attention at with the names of the individuals and organizations participating Those who are not NYSRC ICAP WG Members or Alternate Members will be given an opportunity to comment at the end of each meeting or earlier at the Chairmans invitation Should you have any questions please contact me by email at or by phone at Michael P Hogan Secretary NYSRC ICAP WG
